@@TJvScrollText
<TITLEIMG TJvScrollText>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.LabelsAndStatic
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Can scroll multiple lines of text.
Description
  Use TJvScrollText to scroll multiple lines of text.

  * Use Items to specify the text.
  * Use ScrollDirection to determine how text is scrolled within the control.
  * Use Delay to specify the interval between refresh events.
  * Set Active to true to scroll the text.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.Active
Summary
  Indicates whether the text is scrolling in the control.
Description
  Set Active to true to scroll the text. Set Active to false to interrupt the scrolling.
See Also
  TJvScrollText.Pause, TJvScrollText.Reset, TJvScrollText.Unpause

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.Alignment
Summary
  Determines how the scroll text is aligned within the control.
Description
  The possible values of Alignment are

  <TABLE>
    Value               Meaning
    -----               -------
    taLeftJustify       Text is aligned at the left of the control.
    taCenter            Text is centered in the control.
    taRightJustify      Text is aligned at the right of the control.
  </TABLE>
See Also
  TJvScrollText.Items

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.BackgroundColor
Summary
  Specifies the background color of the control.
Description
  Use Color to read or change the background color of the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.Delay
Summary
  Determines the amount of time, in milliseconds, between two refreshes of the control.
Description
  Delay determines how frequently a refresh of the control occurs. Each time the specified time
  passes, the position of the text on the control changes.

  Use Delay to specify any cardinal value as the interval between refresh events. The default value
  is 50 (1/20 second).
See Also
  TJvScrollText.Active

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.Font
Summary
  \Controls the attributes of the scroll text in the control.
Description
  To change to a new font, specify a new TFont object. To modify a font, change the value of the
  Charset, Color, Height, Name, Pitch, Size, or Style of the TFont object.
See Also
  TJvScrollText.Items

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.Items
Summary
  Contains the strings that appear in the scroll box.
Description
  Use Items to add, insert, delete and move items. Items is of type TStringList. Use this item type
  to access its methods or properties to manipulate the items in the list.
See Also
  TJvScrollText.Font

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.Pause
Summary
  Pauses scrolling the text.
Description
  Call Pause to pause scrolling the text. Pause will decrease ScrollPixels until its equal to 0.
See Also
  TJvScrollText.Reset, TJvScrollText.ScrollPixels, TJvScrollText.Unpause

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.Reset
Summary
  Resets the text position.
Description
  Call \Reset to reposition the text to its start position.
See Also
  TJvScrollText.Pause, TJvScrollText.Unpause

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.ScrollDirection
Summary
  Determines how text is scrolled within the control.
Description
  The possible values of ScrollDirection are

  <TABLE>
    Value               Meaning
    -----               -------
    drFromLeft          Text is scrolled from left to right.
    drFromRight         Text is scrolled from right to left.
    drFromTop           Text is scrolled from top to bottom.
    drFromBottom        Text is scrolled from bottom to top.
  </TABLE>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.ScrollPixels
Summary
  Determines the amount of pixels the text is moved per scroll event.
Description
  Use ScrollPixels to set the number of pixels that the text will move per refresh. If ScrollPixels
  is 0, the text on the control won't move at all.

  The default value for ScrollPixels is 1.
See Also
  Delay

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollText.Unpause
Summary
  Resumes scrolling the text.
Description
  Call Resume to resume scrolling the text. Resume will increase ScrollPixels until its equal to the
  value specified by the user.
See Also
  TJvScrollText.Pause, TJvScrollText.Reset, TJvScrollText.ScrollPixels

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollTextDirection
<TITLE TJvScrollTextDirection type>
Summary
  Enumerates ways text can scroll on a control.
Description
  Use the TJvScrollTextDirection type to specify how text should scroll on a control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollTextDirection.drFromLeft
Text is scrolled from left to right.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollTextDirection.drFromRight
Text is scrolled from right to left.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollTextDirection.drFromTop
Text is scrolled from top to bottom.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollTextDirection.drFromBottom
Text is scrolled from bottom to top.

